  "body": "# ðŸš€ Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nMany users have requested this feature where they could use different graffiti for different validators running in the same client.\r\n\r\nReasons may include:\r\n- Privacy (same graffiti may link validators)\r\n- Fun (graffiti wall, etc)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\nNew validator flag: `--graffiti-file=/path/to/graffitis.yaml`\r\n\r\nSupport for a yaml or JSON mapping that supports the following field types:\r\n- validator index\r\n- validator pubkey (or partial pubkey)\r\n- validator pet-name\r\n- default option or random array option (in place of default)\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\n# /path/to/graffitis.yaml\r\n555: What's up I'm validator 555\r\n1234: yolo\r\n0x0abcef: Partial pubkey match\r\nperfectly-unique-kingfish: My pet name is perfectly-unique-kingfish\r\n\r\n# default OR random could be used\r\ndefault: Mr F was here \r\nrandom:\r\n- Mr A was here\r\n- Mr B was here\r\n- Mr C was here\r\n- graffitiwall:0:0:#000000 \r\n- graffitiwall:1:0:#000000 \r\n```\r\n\r\n### Describe alternatives you've considered\r\n\r\nThere is no alternative for this with a single validator client. \r\nA user would have to run a validator client for each key which complicates their infrastructure and can lead to other issues.\r\n",
